comments: Antetokounmpo (MIL) re-establishes himself slightly in Irving's (DAL) path and some contact occurs as Irving goes under the pick.
Connaughton (MIL) brings his hands towards Williams (DAL) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) brings his forearm towards Lively II (DAL) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
Beasley (MIL) extends his hand into Doncic's (DAL) front and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
Williams (DAL) is firming up in Lillard's (MIL) path and some contact occurs to his slightly extended forearm.
Lopez (MIL) lowers his left arm and makes contact with Irving's (DAL) arm as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Connaughton (MIL) is already in Irving's (DAL) path when contact occurs and he absorbs the contact during the pick.
Doncic (DAL) moves slightly forward towards Lillard (MIL) and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Doncic (DAL) is moving alongside Lillard's (MIL) path and maintains a legal guarding position at the end of the drive.
Williams (DAL) brings his forearm towards Lillard (MIL) and marginal contact occurs as he releases from the contact.
Irving (DAL) gathers the ball on his right foot and does not take more than two steps before passing the ball.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) legally contests Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) jump shot attempt.
Lopez (MIL) and Lively II (DAL) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Possession is awarded to the Mavericks.  Lively II (DAL) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession should have been awarded to the Bucks.
Williams (DAL) is already in Beasley's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the pick.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) advances the ball into the frontcourt within eight seconds.
Lopez (MIL) is firming up in Williams' (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs as the defensive switch occurs.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) places his hand momentarily on Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) side and marginal contact occurs as they move in the same direction.
Williams (DAL) slightly extends his lower body towards Connaughton (MIL) and marginal contact occurs during the screen.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
